buns rise."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Brush tops of risen rolls with oil and sprinkle with poppy seeds. Bake for 15-20 minutes (180°C), until golden brown and cooked through. Transfer rolls onto a wire rack to cool."},{"content":"Place a large frying pan over medium-high heat and add 1 tablespoon oil. Fry patties on both sides until browned and cooked through (approx. 3 minutes per side). Transfer onto a plate and cover to keep warm."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Slice buns into halves horizontally. Place a patty onto bottom half of bun, then top with tomato sauce, lettuce, tomato, avocado (optional) and red onion (optional) to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own tomato sauce, please refer to the recipe in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","4h 40m","6 portions"]}